  "body": "I started geth using the following command\r\n`geth --snapshot=false --cache=4024  --rpc --rpcport 8545 --rpccorsdomain \"*\" --rpcapi eth,net,web3,personal,miner,admin,clique --networkid <network_id> --nat any --allow-insecure-unlock --unlock <my_address> --password \"<password_file>\" --datadir \"node1\" --http --mine`\r\n\r\nIt will start perfectly fine showing logs\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/68948218/117244793-6f720d80-ae59-11eb-9ae0-c919665ad585.png)\r\nBut it start to show following logs all of a sudden which doesn't even make sense.\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/68948218/117244860-8a448200-ae59-11eb-9b08-d282cb26b925.png)\r\nGeth failing to unlock the account continuously is then causing high memory usage and then ultimately server crashes due to out of memory.\r\nI am not sure why its trying to unlock the account which was unlocked initially. I have no idea how to resole the issue.",
