    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> In this particular case, wouldn't vhosts=localhost prevent a browser from connecting?\r\n\r\nNo (and yes). It wouldn't prevent a rogue webpage from making requests, such as submitting a transaction. It would only prevent the rogue webpage from reading the response. \r\n\r\nEDIT to add: If the rogue webpage issues a cors json request to http://localhost/... , then the vhost would be correct, so it would be let through the vhosts filter. Since the `rpccorsdomain` is wildcard, however, it would still have a full bidirectional total communication. \r\n\r\nYour setup is extremely insecure.  ",
